reviewText: I thought this show was about a man with a whip instead of a gun.  Not the case, he uses a gun or fights with a fist....it is just a decent show very much like a 1950 American Western.  No real supporting cast, just Peter Graves running a stagecoach company.  Not a bad show for a rainy day...glad I ordered it.  The set is four DVDS with about ten shows on each.Quick update the more you watch the show the more you will like it.  I even have grown to like the intro theme song.

reviewText: This is just about the only western series which is set in Australia and it truely captures the flavour of our early colonial days. The stories are interesting and well paced and the main character played by Peter Graves is entirely believable as the founder of the Cobb and Co stageline.

reviewText: I recently purchased WHIPLASH a 1961 Australian TV show set in the 19th century about an historical figure who started the stagecoach lines and trading stores in Australia. Christopher Cobb is played by actor Peter Graves best known for Mission Impossible TV series. Wonderful transfer from 16 mm to DVDs. Very happy with this product and I'd been searching for it for many years. All black and white as was originally filmed, but if you are a Peter Graves' fan, this is a worthwhile series to add to your collection.

reviewText: Quality of Whiplash was fantastic; however, I found it boring and understood why it only lasted one season at the most two.  I'm a fan of westerns but this was not up to par.  I see where a lot could have been done with it but the writers and/or directors failed.  It seems to be missing...  That's my reason for a rating of 3; "OK".  Had I known it was "OK" I would not have purchased.  I maybe of the minority opinion but that's my review.
